name: Monterey Co Health
tweet: Let's talk #turkey!  According to a study by the food safety experts at the USDA, washing or rinsing raw turkey can put you at risk of foodborne illness. There's only one time you should wash a raw turkey, and that is after brining. Otherwise, do not wash a turkey before cooking.  https://t.co/rcGglAf9dR
